 {
  "doctype": "EasyEcom Field Mapping",
  "name": "EasyEcom-Item-Pull",
  "mapping_name": "EasyEcom-Item-Pull",
  "entity_type": "Item",
  "direction": "Pull",
  "active": 1,
  "missing_field_policy": "Permissive",
  "version": 2,
  "last_modified_by": "Administrator",
  "last_modified_at": "2026-05-26 00:00:00",
  "change_reason": "Stage 2 reconciliation against real captured GetProductMaster payloads (tests/ee_mock/getproductmaster_response.json, getproductmaster_child_product.json). Replaces the stale Bidirectional EasyEcom-Item-Sync ruleset which had: wrong source paths (base_uom -> EE actually sends accounting_unit; weight_grams -> EE actually sends weight); missing fields (cost, mrp, size, colour, dimensions, brand, active, ee_product_id, ee_cp_id); no transform for the EE active->ERPNext disabled flip; a placeholder compose ref to EasyEcom-Item-UOM-Sync which is empty and not used in Stage 2. The matching push ruleset (EasyEcom-Item-Push) is a Stage 3 build.",
  "rules": [
   {
    "erpnext_path": "item_code",
    "easyecom_path": "sku",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "required": 1,
    "notes": "EE's sku is the unique identifier per its FAQ; we use it as item_code on create. Stage 2 \u00a78.1.3 matches sku==item_code byte-for-byte."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "item_name",
    "easyecom_path": "product_name",
    "transform_push": "str_strip",
    "transform_pull": "str_strip",
    "required": 1
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "description",
    "easyecom_path": "description",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "gst_hsn_code",
    "easyecom_path": "hsn_code",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "notes": "HSN gating handled by the FLOW (item_pull.py). The ruleset passes the value through; the flow checks whether the HSN exists in tabGST HSN Code and Flag-Not-Creates the product when absent (India Compliance makes HSN-less Item un-createable; we do not placeholder per \u00a78.1.4). We avoid validate_against on the rule because it would raise mid-rule and prevent the flow from reading the other fields it needs for the FNC map row's diagnostic context."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "stock_uom",
    "easyecom_path": "accounting_unit",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "notes": "EE's accounting_unit is dirty in real payloads (mob000=111, Top3=333, Nike=11, SKINQ=PCS, child product NA). The FLOW checks whether the produced value matches a real UOM doc; if not, substitutes the Account's default_uom and flags the Item as Created-Flagged. The substitution doesn't happen in the ruleset because the validity check requires a DB lookup against tabUOM and the flag-or-not decision is flow-level."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "disabled",
    "easyecom_path": "active",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "conditional_constant",
    "transform_args": {
     "conditions": [
      {
       "when": "source_payload.get('active') in (1, '1', True)",
       "then": 0
      }
     ],
     "default": 1
    },
    "notes": "Flips polarity: EE active=1 (alive) maps to ERPNext disabled=0; EE active=0 (dead) maps to disabled=1. Uses conditional_constant rather than enum_map because EE's int 1 wouldn't match a JSON map key (always str), and to handle both '1'/'0' string and 1/0 int defensively."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "weight_per_unit",
    "easyecom_path": "weight",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float",
    "notes": "EE weight is in grams; ERPNext weight_per_unit takes a Float; weight_uom set as a custom-field convention since we don't write into Item.weight_uom on pull."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_height_cm",
    "easyecom_path": "height",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_length_cm",
    "easyecom_path": "length",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_width_cm",
    "easyecom_path": "width",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_ee_cost",
    "easyecom_path": "cost",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float",
    "notes": "EE cost stored on Item for visibility; NOT written into Item.valuation_rate (auto-managed by ERPNext stock ledger)."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "standard_rate",
    "easyecom_path": "mrp",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float",
    "notes": "EE MRP = ERPNext default selling rate (best-fit)."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_ee_mrp",
    "easyecom_path": "mrp",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float",
    "notes": "Preserve the original EE MRP independent of standard_rate (which the FDE may later override)."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_size",
    "easyecom_path": "size",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_colour",
    "easyecom_path": "colour",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_ee_product_id",
    "easyecom_path": "product_id",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "int_to_str"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_ee_cp_id",
    "easyecom_path": "cp_id",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "int_to_str"
   }
  ]
 },
 {
  "doctype": "EasyEcom Field Mapping",
  "name": "EasyEcom-Item-Push",
  "mapping_name": "EasyEcom-Item-Push",
  "entity_type": "Item",
  "direction": "Push",
  "active": 1,
  "missing_field_policy": "Permissive",
  "version": 2,
  "last_modified_by": "Administrator",
  "last_modified_at": "2026-05-26 12:00:00",
  "change_reason": "\u00a78d Stage 3 \u2014 ERPNext Item \u2192 EasyEcom CreateMasterProduct / UpdateMasterProduct payload. Holds the REAL-DATA-FROM-ITEM mappings only (Sku, ItemName, ProductTaxCode, dimensions, Cost, productId for updates). The MANUFACTURED EE-mandatory fields ERPNext doesn't carry (materialType=1 Finished Good, itemType=0 normal in Stage 3, Brand/Category/ModelNumber fallbacks, TaxRate snapped to EE's allowed {0,3,5,12,18,28} set) are injected by the FLOW (item_push.py) after the engine produces this payload \u2014 they're flow decisions, not translations, and don't belong in the ruleset per the \u00a78.0 engine-as-translator policy. Stage 3 covers normal products only; bundles (combo_product) are Stage 4's job and use itemType=1 + subProducts. | v2 (FDE-configurability refactor per user direction): the manufactured constants (materialType=1, itemType=0, Brand fallback, Cost fallback chain, ModelNumber=item_code) are now ruleset rules instead of flow-code constants. FDE edits them via the desk EasyEcom Field Mapping > EasyEcom-Item-Push > Rules child table \u2014 no code deploy needed to change defaults or add company-conditional logic. TaxRate stays in the flow (it's a DB lookup + snap-to-set, not a constant or simple derivation).",
  "rules": [
   {
    "erpnext_path": "item_code",
    "easyecom_path": "Sku",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "required": 1,
    "notes": "EE's Sku is its primary key for products (per its FAQ). ERPNext's item_code is the byte-for-byte source \u2014 the \u00a78d pull also uses sku==item_code for auto-mapping."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "item_name",
    "easyecom_path": "ItemName",
    "transform_push": "str_strip",
    "transform_pull": "str_strip"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "description",
    "easyecom_path": "Description",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "gst_hsn_code",
    "easyecom_path": "ProductTaxCode",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "notes": "Item.gst_hsn_code is required on Item save (India Compliance), so a successfully-saved Item always has it. The flow doesn't need to re-check; an item without HSN would never reach push."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "brand",
    "easyecom_path": "Brand",
    "transform_push": "custom_python",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "notes": "EE requires Brand on Create. If Item.brand is set (Link to Brand DocType), push its name; otherwise fall back to 'Unbranded'. FDE: edit transform_args.expression in this rule's row to change the fallback string (e.g. 'House Brand') or add company-conditional logic. The pull direction is identity \u2014 EE-side brand strings land on Item.brand and a Brand row gets auto-created later by a Stage-5 cleanup if needed.",
    "transform_args": {
     "expression": "value if value else 'Unbranded'"
    }
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "item_group",
    "easyecom_path": "Category",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "notes": "ERPNext Item.item_group is required, so this always has a value. Pushed as Category \u2014 EE will create/lookup its own side category from the string."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "weight_per_unit",
    "easyecom_path": "Weight",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float",
    "notes": "Grams. Flow flags item Not-Pushed if missing."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_length_cm",
    "easyecom_path": "Length",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_height_cm",
    "easyecom_path": "Height",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_width_cm",
    "easyecom_path": "Width",
    "transform_push": "float_to_str",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_ee_cost",
    "easyecom_path": "Cost",
    "transform_push": "custom_python",
    "transform_pull": "str_to_float",
    "notes": "Prefer the EE-origin cost captured at pull time (ecs_ee_cost). Fall back to Item.valuation_rate when the item was ERPNext-originated (never pulled). Final fallback: 0 (EE accepts). FDE: edit transform_args.expression to change the fallback chain \u2014 e.g. add 'last_purchase_rate' if your sourcing prefers the most recent PO.",
    "transform_args": {
     "expression": "value if value else (source_doc.valuation_rate or 0)"
    }
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_ee_product_id",
    "easyecom_path": "productId",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "notes": "Only meaningful on Update calls (UpdateMasterProduct keys on sku OR productId). On Create the field is absent on the Item until EE returns the product_id and the flow writes it back to the map row + Item.ecs_ee_product_id."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "ecs_ee_cp_id",
    "easyecom_path": "cpId",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity"
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "item_code",
    "easyecom_path": "ModelNumber",
    "transform_push": "identity",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "notes": "ERPNext Item has no native model_no field; we use item_code as ModelNumber for EE (uniquely identifying, always present). FDE: change transform_push to 'custom_python' with a different expression if your client maintains a separate model-number custom field (e.g. \"source_doc.ecs_model_no or source_doc.item_code\")."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "item_code",
    "easyecom_path": "materialType",
    "transform_push": "conditional_constant",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "transform_args": {
     "conditions": [
      {
       "when": "True",
       "then": 1
      }
     ],
     "default": 1
    },
    "notes": "EE-mandatory on Create; absent from ERPNext Item. Default 1 (Finished Good) \u2014 per \u00a78.1.5 / packet's stated default. The rule's erpnext_path is item_code as a trigger source (the transform ignores the value and returns the constant); EE-side is materialType.\nFDE: edit transform_args.default (or add a condition) to change the value \u2014 e.g. raw materials = 2, or company-specific via 'source_doc.item_group in (\"Raw\", ...)' \u2192 2. No code deploy needed."
   },
   {
    "erpnext_path": "item_code",
    "easyecom_path": "itemType",
    "transform_push": "conditional_constant",
    "transform_pull": "identity",
    "transform_args": {
     "conditions": [
      {
       "when": "True",
       "then": 0
      }
     ],
     "default": 0
    },
    "notes": "EE itemType: Child=0 (normal), Combo=1, Kit=2. Stage 3 ships 0 for normal products; Stage 4 (bundles) will swap this rule to a conditional that returns 1 when source_doc is a Product Bundle wrapper. FDE: only change manually if your data has non-standard semantics \u2014 Stage 4 will land the proper Bundle-aware condition."
   }
  ]
 },
